---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { socials } from '../config';

const interests = [
  'Identity and access',
  'ISO 27001 and GRC',
  'Single-player worlds',
  'Graphics from scratch',
  'Godot game dev',
  'Understanding systems all the way down',
];
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="Who I am and what keeps me curious.">
  <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
  <div class="wayrule"></div>
  <h1 class="display h1">Hello.</h1>

  <p class="lede">I am Akil. I look after security and identity for a distributed team. I came to it
    the long way, through engineering.</p>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>These days I lead IT systems and cybersecurity at Teams Squared, a global remote staffing firm
      that places skilled professionals from emerging markets into teams at client companies worldwide.
      It started legal-first and is now multi-industry. I work out of Colombo, and in practice I own the
      internal things that decide who can touch what. Identity on Entra ID, conditional access, endpoint
      security, and an organization-wide ISO 27001 ISMS for a team spread across several countries. I like this work more than I expected to. It rewards being
      careful, and asking the unglamorous question. Who still has access here, and why.</p>
    <p>I did not start in security. I started by building things. I have a computer science degree
      from Dalhousie, and I still write most of the software my team runs on, from an internal
      training platform to a device tracker to the client portal I inherited and now look after.
      Coming up through engineering is the reason the security side makes sense to me. I have built
      the systems I am now trying to protect, so I know where they leak.</p>
    <p>Before any of this I spent a co-op term at Ubisoft Halifax writing gameplay code in Unity and
      C#. Games are still where most of my after-hours curiosity goes. I make small game and graphics
      projects for the pleasure of it, including a shooter built around one stubborn idea and
      renderers written straight against Vulkan and OpenGL, because I wanted to know how a triangle
      actually becomes a pixel.</p>
    <p>The thread through all of it is the same. I like understanding a system far enough down that
      it stops feeling like magic, and I like building things that still work when nobody is watching
      them. When I am not doing that, I am usually deep in a single-player world or tinkering in
      Godot.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="sec-label" id="looking">What I'm looking for</h2>
  <p class="seeking">Open to roles in security and identity, or software engineering close to it, and
    happy to keep wearing more than one hat. I hold a Canadian post-graduation work permit valid
    through June 2029 and am open to relocating anywhere in Canada, including through the Atlantic
    Immigration Program. If that sounds like a fit, I would like to hear from you.</p>

  <h2 class="sec-label">What keeps me curious</h2>
  <ul class="interests">
    {interests.map((i) => <li>{i}</li>)}
  </ul>

  <h2 class="sec-label">Elsewhere</h2>
  <ul class="contact">
    {socials.map((s) => (
      <li>
        <span class="c-label">{s.label}</span>
        <a href={s.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{s.handle ?? s.label}</a>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .h1 { font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.4rem); margin-top: var(--space-1); }
  .lede {
    font-size: 1.0625rem; color: var(--ink-muted); line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 58ch; margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }
  .prose { max-width: var(--measure); margin-top: var(--space-3); }
  .prose p { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); color: var(--ink); }
  .seeking {
    max-width: var(--measure); margin-top: var(--space-2); color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.6;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--cobalt); padding-left: var(--space-2);
  }
  .sec-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-muted);
    margin: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-2);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    scroll-margin-top: 5rem;
  }
  .interests { list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .interests li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--ink-muted);
    background: var(--paper-panel); padding: 5px 11px;
  }
  .contact { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-top: var(--space-2); max-width: 32rem; }
  .contact li {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 7rem 1fr; gap: var(--space-2);
    padding: var(--space-1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8125rem; align-items: baseline;
  }
  .contact li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .c-label { color: var(--ink-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-size: 0.6875rem; }
  .contact a { color: var(--cobalt); text-decoration: none; word-break: break-word; }
  .contact a:hover { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .contact li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2px; }
  }
</style>
